cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.AI. 

The paper proposes a continuation algorithm for nonsmooth regularized risk minimization problems, which are commonly studied in the field of machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the proposed algorithm can be applied to classification and regression tasks. The paper also mentions experiments and comparisons with state-of-the-art methods, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
